          T R A C K E R

Plans for future:

1. Program: 303tracker.
   Release: december 1997 at Aminet and HTTP://www.xs4all.nl/~mjk303.
   ------------------------------------------------------------------

New plan= 303tracker: a follow up of 303emu. A while ago it was mentioned
to be the tracker-editor plug-in for the never released 303emu V2.5. But
bcoz I noticed, that the 303tracker is so powerful to use that you don't
need 303emu, the main-program, anymore at all, I decided to drop the 303emu
and continue developing 303tracker.

303tracker is a TB-303 render-program with a 'Protracker' interface. The
first release will be NON-realtime, although it WILL have some pseudo-
realtime routines to test a pattern, play a song, tweak a slider... just
like with the knobs in 303emu V2.3z.

On the versions after this first one, there will be worked on a REALTIME
engine. Maybe his time, when it sounds good, I'll release it commercial.

2. Program: 303envelope editor.
   Release: december 1997 at Aminet and HTTP://www.xs4all.nl/~mjk303.
   ------------------------------------------------------------------

Also promised as plug-in for 303emuV2.5, this will be a very weird nice
super-easy stand-alone program.


3. Program: BAMI 303.
   Release: probably never.
   ------------------------

ABOUT 'BAMI 303': I am not quite sure what I want to do with it. In fact
'303tracker' is another name for 'BAMI 303'. Besides that, 'BAMI 303' was
mentioned to be a realtime TB-303 program, while 303tracker isn't in its
first release, although later versions will be realtime. So I think I'll
flush (read THROW AWAY) 'BAMI 303', and we call it from now on '303
tracker'. Allright?

4. Program: 303emuV2.5.
   Release: NEVER.
   --------------------

As said b4, 303emuV2.x will be stopped. Hoora!


